<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="920" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d920">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2771.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of War</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following telegram * * * from commanding general central division dated
                            Chicago, Ill., February 11, 1912, repeated for your information: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Steever wires to department headquarters, 10th: “Turned Mexican
                                    prisoners, captured Noria, over to proper civil authorities.
                                    Retained arms and mounts at request Mexican consul, who claims
                                    belong to his Government. Recommend they be delivered to him. *
                                    * *”</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Potts</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Commanding</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>